Brainware LLC Privacy Policy
Brainware LLC will respect your privacy. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use and protect your personal information.
Besides the information Brainware LLC itself collects, we use various third parties to distribute our apps. These organizations will also collect and use information obtained in the process. Brainware LLC also has access to and may use some of this information. This is governed by the third parties respective privacy policies.
We collect and retain:
information you send to us by e-mail
information necessary to keep track of your product purchases (this includes your account name and a unique device identifier)
anonymous statistics on the usage of our websites, apps and software
We may use this information to:
provide customer support
verify the purchasing status of a product
improve our website and products
We will only share this information:
if we have a good-faith belief that this is necessary to meet any applicable law, regulation, legal process or enforceable governmental request or to protect against harm to the rights, property or safety of Brainware LLC, our users or the public as required or permitted by law.
We might change this privacy policy in future. Such changes will be communicated via this website and old versions will be retained for your reference.
Note: This privacy policy also applies to the iOS app developed by Brainware LLC named Video Poker Trainer by Ron Schweitzer.